cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DB, cs.PL 

The paper discusses data provenance and security monitoring, which are topics commonly found in the computer security (cs.CR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The paper also presents an architecture for capturing data provenance in web services, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and database (cs.DB) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the non-invasive deployment of provenance capabilities, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL).
